<paragraph blockId="0.[151,1437,652,1719]" pageId="0" pageNumber="592">
<materialsCitation collectorName="SE Asia" country="Austria" location="South American" pageId="0" pageNumber="592" specimenCount="1" typeStatus="holotype">
Two species of 
<taxonomicName _evidence="catalogs" _step="genera" authority="Papp &amp; Foldvari, 2001" authorityName="Papp &amp; Foldvari" authorityYear="2001" box="[324,687,652,676]" class="Insecta" family="Hybotidae" genus="Chvalaea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="592" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[324,426,652,676]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="592">Chvalaea</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Papp, L. &amp; Foldvari, M." box="[436,687,653,676]" pageId="0" pageNumber="592" pagination="349 - 361" refId="ref1043" refString="Papp, L. &amp; Foldvari, M. (2001) A new genus and three new species of Hybotidae with new records of the Hungarian Empidoidea (Diptera). Acta Zoologica Academiae Scientiarum Hungaricae, 47 (4), 349 - 361." type="journal article" year="2001">Papp &amp; Földvári, 2001</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
are known from Europe. 
<taxonomicName _evidence="catalogs" _step="species1" authority="(Strobl, 1910)" baseAuthorityName="Strobl" baseAuthorityYear="1910" box="[974,1390,652,676]" class="Insecta" family="Hybotidae" genus="Chvalaea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="592" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rugosiventris">
<emphasis box="[974,1227,652,676]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="592">Chvalaea rugosiventris</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Strobl, P. G." box="[1243,1382,653,676]" pageId="0" pageNumber="592" pagination="45 - 293" refId="ref1153" refString="Strobl, P. G. (1910) Die Dipteren von Steiermark. II. Nachtrag. Mitteilungen des Naturwissenschaftlichen Vereines fur Steiermark, 46 (1909), 45 - 293. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 8540" type="journal article" year="1910">Strobl, 1910</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
, the type species of the genus, was originally described as a species of 
<taxonomicName _evidence="catalogs" _step="genera" authority="Macquart, 1827" authorityName="Macquart" authorityYear="1827" box="[865,1152,688,711]" class="Insecta" family="Hybotidae" genus="Leptopeza" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="592" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[865,974,688,711]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="592">Leptopeza</emphasis>
Macquart, 1827
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Strobl, P. G." box="[1166,1297,688,711]" pageId="0" pageNumber="592" pagination="45 - 293" refId="ref1153" refString="Strobl, P. G. (1910) Die Dipteren von Steiermark. II. Nachtrag. Mitteilungen des Naturwissenschaftlichen Vereines fur Steiermark, 46 (1909), 45 - 293. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 8540" type="journal article" year="1910">Strobl 1910</bibRefCitation>
). It was long known only by the 
<typeStatus box="[367,460,722,745]" pageId="0" pageNumber="592">holotype</typeStatus>
male from 
<collectingCountry box="[592,673,722,745]" name="Austria" pageId="0" pageNumber="592">Austria</collectingCountry>
, but today it is known also from 
<collectingCountry box="[1044,1122,722,745]" name="Croatia" pageId="0" pageNumber="592">Croatia</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[1180,1272,722,745]" name="Hungary" pageId="0" pageNumber="592">Hungary</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Chvala, M." box="[1289,1431,722,745]" pageId="0" pageNumber="592" pagination="1 - 279" refId="ref860" refString="Chvala, M. (1983) The Empidoidea (Diptera) of Fennoscandia and Denmark. II. General Part. The Families Hybotidae, Atelestidae and Microphoridae. Fauna Entomologica Scandinavica, 12, 1 - 279." type="journal article" year="1983">Chvála 1983</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Chvala, M." box="[151,208,757,780]" pageId="0" pageNumber="592" pagination="163 - 186" refId="ref900" refString="Chvala, M. (2003) Revision of the Hybotidae (Diptera) described by Gabriel Strobl from the Alps, with an annotated list of Strobl's localities and notes on the Admont Collection. Acta Universitatis Carolinae Biologica, 47, 163 - 186." type="journal article" year="2003">2003</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Papp, L. &amp; Foldvari, M." box="[219,462,757,780]" pageId="0" pageNumber="592" pagination="349 - 361" refId="ref1043" refString="Papp, L. &amp; Foldvari, M. (2001) A new genus and three new species of Hybotidae with new records of the Hungarian Empidoidea (Diptera). Acta Zoologica Academiae Scientiarum Hungaricae, 47 (4), 349 - 361." type="journal article" year="2001">Papp &amp; Földvári 2001</bibRefCitation>
). 
<bibRefCitation author="Sinclair, B. J. &amp; Cumming, J. M." box="[481,802,757,780]" pageId="0" pageNumber="592" pagination="161 - 186" refId="ref1090" refString="Sinclair, B. J. &amp; Cumming, J. M. (2000) Revision of the genus Apterodromia (Diptera: Empidoidea), with a redefinition of the tribe Ocydromiini. Records of the Australian Museum, 52, 161 - 186. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.3853 / j. 0067 - 1975.52.2000.1313" type="journal article" year="2000">Sinclair and Cumming (2000)</bibRefCitation>
first recognised 
<taxonomicName _evidence="catalogs" _step="genera" box="[982,1084,756,780]" class="Insecta" family="Hybotidae" genus="Chvalaea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="592" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[982,1084,756,780]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="592">Chvalaea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as “undescribed genus B”. 
<bibRefCitation author="Papp, L. &amp; Foldvari, M." pageId="0" pageNumber="592" pagination="349 - 361" refId="ref1043" refString="Papp, L. &amp; Foldvari, M. (2001) A new genus and three new species of Hybotidae with new records of the Hungarian Empidoidea (Diptera). Acta Zoologica Academiae Scientiarum Hungaricae, 47 (4), 349 - 361." type="journal article" year="2001">Papp and Földvári (2001)</bibRefCitation>
subsequently described the genus and added a second European species, 
<taxonomicName _evidence="catalogs" _step="species1" authority="Papp &amp; Foldvari, 2001" authorityName="Papp &amp; Foldvari" authorityYear="2001" class="Insecta" family="Hybotidae" genus="Chvalaea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="592" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sopianae">
<emphasis box="[1144,1349,791,815]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="592">Chvalaea sopianae</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Papp, L. &amp; Foldvari, M." pageId="0" pageNumber="592" pagination="349 - 361" refId="ref1043" refString="Papp, L. &amp; Foldvari, M. (2001) A new genus and three new species of Hybotidae with new records of the Hungarian Empidoidea (Diptera). Acta Zoologica Academiae Scientiarum Hungaricae, 47 (4), 349 - 361." type="journal article" year="2001">Papp &amp; Földvári, 2001</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, from 
<collectingCountry box="[384,479,826,849]" name="Hungary" pageId="0" pageNumber="592">Hungary</collectingCountry>
. Five additional species of 
<taxonomicName _evidence="catalogs" _step="genera" box="[775,877,825,849]" class="Insecta" family="Hybotidae" genus="Chvalaea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="592" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[775,877,825,849]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="592">Chvalaea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
have recently been described by 
<bibRefCitation author="Ale-Rocha, R." box="[1241,1435,826,849]" pageId="0" pageNumber="592" pagination="17 - 30" refId="ref766" refString="Ale-Rocha, R. (2006) First description of species of Chvalaea Papp &amp; Foldvari from the Neotropical Region (Diptera, Hybotidae, Ocydromiinae). Zootaxa, 1167, 17 - 30." type="journal article" year="2006">Ale-Rocha (2006)</bibRefCitation>
from the Neotropics, including the first description of males of the genus. The genus is also known from 
<collectingCountry box="[1287,1351,861,884]" name="China" pageId="0" pageNumber="592">China</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectorName pageId="0" pageNumber="592">SE Asia</collectorName>
from unpublished records (Adrian Plant, pers. comm.). 
<bibRefCitation author="Ale-Rocha, R." box="[807,1001,896,919]" pageId="0" pageNumber="592" pagination="410 - 412" refId="ref802" refString="Ale-Rocha, R. (2007) Redescription of Oropezella abdominalis Collin from Chile with description of the male and a key to the Neotropical genera of Ocydromiinae. Revista Brasileira de Entomologica, 51 (4), 410 - 412. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1590 / s 0085 - 56262007000400003" type="journal article" year="2007">Ale-Rocha (2007)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Cumming, J. M. &amp; Sinclair, B. J." box="[1055,1377,896,919]" pageId="0" pageNumber="592" refId="ref947" refString="Cumming, J. M. &amp; Sinclair, B. J. (2009) Empididae (dance flies, balloon flies, predaceous flies). In: Brown, B. V., Borkent, A., Cumming, J. M., Wood, D. M., Woodley, N. E. &amp; Zumbado, M. A. (Eds.), Manual of Central American Diptera. Vol. 1. NRC Research Press, Ottawa, pp. 653 - 670." type="book" year="2009">Cumming and Sinclair (2009)</bibRefCitation>
have published keys for separating 
<taxonomicName _evidence="catalogs" _step="genera" box="[475,577,929,953]" class="Insecta" family="Hybotidae" genus="Chvalaea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="592" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[475,577,929,953]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="592">Chvalaea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<taxonomicName _evidence="catalogs" _step="genera" authorityName="Collin" authorityYear="1926" box="[644,761,929,953]" class="Insecta" family="Hybotidae" genus="Oropezella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="592" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[644,761,929,953]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="592">Oropezella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
based on 
<location box="[873,1048,930,953]" country="Austria" name="South American" pageId="0" pageNumber="592">South American</location>
material, but they are also valid for the currently known European species of these genera. 
<taxonomicName _evidence="catalogs" _step="species1" authorityName="Papp &amp; Foldvari" authorityYear="2001" box="[799,1012,964,988]" class="Insecta" family="Hybotidae" genus="Chvalaea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="592" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sopianae">
<emphasis box="[799,1012,964,988]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="592">Chvalaea sopianae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
keys out, somewhat uneasily, as an 
<taxonomicName _evidence="catalogs" _step="genera" authorityName="Collin" authorityYear="1926" box="[151,269,999,1023]" class="Insecta" family="Hybotidae" genus="Oropezella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="592" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,269,999,1023]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="592">Oropezella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in 
<bibRefCitation author="Chvala, M." box="[301,457,1000,1023]" pageId="0" pageNumber="592" pagination="1 - 279" refId="ref860" refString="Chvala, M. (1983) The Empidoidea (Diptera) of Fennoscandia and Denmark. II. General Part. The Families Hybotidae, Atelestidae and Microphoridae. Fauna Entomologica Scandinavica, 12, 1 - 279." type="journal article" year="1983">Chvála (1983)</bibRefCitation>
. It differs from true 
<taxonomicName _evidence="catalogs" _step="genera" authorityName="Collin" authorityYear="1926" box="[670,787,999,1023]" class="Insecta" family="Hybotidae" genus="Oropezella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="592" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[670,787,999,1023]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="592">Oropezella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the heavily sclerotized and rugose abdomen, hooked hind tarsi and the lack of acrostichal and dorsocentral setae on the mesonotum
</materialsCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="0.[151,1437,652,1719]" pageId="0" pageNumber="592">
<materialsCitation country="Finland" latitude="62.996666" location="The forest" longLatPrecision="101" longitude="31.253334" pageId="0" pageNumber="592" specimenCount="1">
The Finnish expert group 
<collectedFrom box="[481,595,1069,1092]" pageId="0" pageNumber="592">
on 
<taxonomicName _evidence="catalogs" _step="order" box="[515,595,1069,1092]" class="Magnoliopsida" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="592" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="order">Diptera</taxonomicName>
</collectedFrom>
organized a field collecting trip to Ilomantsi, the easternmost municipality of 
<collectingCountry box="[151,233,1106,1129]" name="Finland" pageId="0" pageNumber="592">Finland</collectingCountry>
in the summer of 2008. On June 24 
<superScript attach="left" box="[615,626,1104,1116]" fontSize="5" pageId="0" pageNumber="592">th</superScript>
we visited an old forest stand in Pampalo, Ilomantsi, some 
<quantity box="[1263,1337,1106,1129]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.5" pageId="0" pageNumber="592" unit="km" value="1.5">1.5 km</quantity>
NNW of the Pampalo gold mine (
<geoCoordinate box="[421,537,1141,1164]" degrees="62" direction="north" minutes="59.8" orientation="latitude" pageId="0" pageNumber="592" precision="92" value="62.996666">62°59.8’N</geoCoordinate>
, 
<geoCoordinate box="[550,663,1141,1164]" degrees="31" direction="east" minutes="15.2" orientation="longitude" pageId="0" pageNumber="592" precision="92" value="31.253334">31°15.2’E</geoCoordinate>
). 
<location box="[684,795,1141,1164]" country="Finland" latitude="62.996666" longLatPrecision="101" longitude="31.253334" name="The forest" pageId="0" pageNumber="592">The forest</location>
stand was dominated by mature Norwegian spruce (
<taxonomicName _evidence="catalogs" _step="species1" class="Pinopsida" family="Pinaceae" genus="Picea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Pinales" pageId="0" pageNumber="592" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="abies">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="592">Picea abies</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). Old deciduous trees, mostly birch (
<taxonomicName box="[603,725,1175,1199]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Betulaceae" genus="Betula" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fagales" pageId="0" pageNumber="592" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis box="[603,672,1175,1199]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="592">Betula</emphasis>
spp.
</taxonomicName>
) and aspen (
<taxonomicName _evidence="catalogs" _step="species1" box="[860,1036,1175,1199]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Salicaceae" genus="Populus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="0" pageNumber="592" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="tremula">
<emphasis box="[860,1036,1175,1199]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="592">Populus tremula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) were also present in lesser numbers. The soil humidity varied from saturated depressions to relatively well drained soils on the upper slopes of low ridges. The highest fly diversity was found on the lower ridge slopes where dead wood was abundant. A large, slender hybotid fly was swept, netted by the author from the trunk of a decaying aspen log. The specimen (
<figureCitation box="[1123,1185,1280,1303]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="1.[151,255,1678,1702]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,194,1654]" captionTargetId="figure-94@1.[151,1436,194,1654]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURE 1. A female Chvalaea sopianae Papp &amp; Földvári, 2001 from eastern Finland (specimen jka08-00169). Scale bar = 1 mm." pageId="0" pageNumber="592">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
) was later identified as a female of 
<taxonomicName _evidence="catalogs" _step="species1" authorityName="Papp &amp; Foldvari" authorityYear="2001" box="[277,482,1313,1337]" class="Insecta" family="Hybotidae" genus="Chvalaea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="592" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sopianae">
<emphasis box="[277,482,1313,1337]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="592">Chvalaea sopianae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. It is currently stored in the author’s private 
<taxonomicName _evidence="catalogs" _step="order" box="[958,1038,1314,1337]" class="Magnoliopsida" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="592" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="order">Diptera</taxonomicName>
collection as specimen jka08-00169
</materialsCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="0.[151,1437,652,1719]" pageId="0" pageNumber="592">
The Pampalo old forest stand proved to be interesting from a dipterological point of view. In addition to 
<taxonomicName _evidence="catalogs" _step="genera" box="[1327,1429,1348,1372]" class="Insecta" family="Hybotidae" genus="Chvalaea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="592" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1327,1429,1348,1372]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="592">Chvalaea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, several noteworthy saproxylic 
<taxonomicName _evidence="catalogs" _step="order" box="[477,557,1384,1407]" class="Magnoliopsida" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="592" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="order">Diptera</taxonomicName>
were recorded from the site. 
<taxonomicName _evidence="catalogs" _step="species1" authority="(Pleske, 1925)" baseAuthorityName="Pleske" baseAuthorityYear="1925" box="[868,1244,1383,1407]" class="Insecta" family="Xylophagidae" genus="Xylophagus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="592" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kowarzi">
<emphasis box="[868,1085,1383,1407]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="592">Xylophagus kowarzi</emphasis>
(Pleske, 1925)
</taxonomicName>
was numerous on fallen trunks of deciduous trees. Larvae and copulating pairs of this fly were taken from aspen logs. Empty puparia of 
<taxonomicName _evidence="catalogs" _step="species1" authority="Pleske, 1925" authorityName="Pleske" authorityYear="1925" box="[151,553,1452,1476]" class="Insecta" family="Xylomyidae" genus="Xylomya" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="592" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="czekanovskii">
<emphasis box="[151,394,1452,1476]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="592">Xylomya czekanovskii</emphasis>
Pleske, 1925
</taxonomicName>
were found under aspen bark. Sweep-netting yielded another rare hybotid, 
<taxonomicName _evidence="catalogs" _step="species1" authority="Tuomikoski, 1936" authorityName="Tuomikoski" authorityYear="1936" box="[151,642,1487,1511]" class="Insecta" family="Hybotidae" genus="Leptodromiella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="592" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="crassiseta">
<emphasis box="[151,431,1487,1511]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="592">Leptodromiella crassiseta</emphasis>
Tuomikoski, 1936
</taxonomicName>
, the syrphid 
<taxonomicName _evidence="catalogs" _step="species1" authority="(Zetterstedt, 1843)" baseAuthorityName="Zetterstedt" baseAuthorityYear="1843" box="[789,1186,1487,1511]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Lejota" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="592" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ruficornis">
<emphasis box="[789,973,1487,1511]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="592">Lejota ruficornis</emphasis>
(Zetterstedt, 1843)
</taxonomicName>
, and no less than five species of clusiids: 
<taxonomicName _evidence="catalogs" _step="species1" authority="(Zetterstedt, 1848)" baseAuthorityName="Zetterstedt" baseAuthorityYear="1848" box="[362,767,1521,1545]" class="Insecta" family="Clusiidae" genus="Clusiodes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="592" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="apicalis">
<emphasis box="[362,559,1521,1545]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="592">Clusiodes apicalis</emphasis>
(Zetterstedt, 1848)
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName _evidence="catalog+fontStyle" _step="styledSpecies" authority="Tuomikoski, 1933" authorityName="Tuomikoski" authorityYear="1933" box="[782,1065,1521,1545]" class="Insecta" family="Clusiidae" genus="Clusiodes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="592" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="freyi">
<emphasis box="[782,862,1521,1545]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="592">C. freyi</emphasis>
Tuomikoski, 1933
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName _evidence="catalog+fontStyle" _step="styledSpecies" authority="(Fallen, 1823)" baseAuthorityName="Fallen" baseAuthorityYear="1823" box="[1080,1397,1522,1545]" class="Insecta" family="Clusiidae" genus="Clusiodes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="592" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="geomyzinus">
<emphasis box="[1080,1237,1522,1545]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="592">C. geomyzinus</emphasis>
(Fallén, 1823)
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName _evidence="catalog+fontStyle" _step="styledSpecies" authority="(Zetterstedt, 1855)" baseAuthorityName="Zetterstedt" baseAuthorityYear="1855" class="Insecta" family="Clusiidae" genus="Clusiodes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="592" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pictipes">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="592">C. pictipes</emphasis>
(Zetterstedt, 1855)
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName _evidence="catalog+fontStyle" _step="styledSpecies" authority="(Meigen, 1830)" baseAuthorityName="Meigen" baseAuthorityYear="1830" box="[501,812,1556,1580]" class="Insecta" family="Clusiidae" genus="Clusiodes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="592" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ruficollis">
<emphasis box="[501,631,1556,1580]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="592">C. ruficollis</emphasis>
(Meigen, 1830)
</taxonomicName>
. This small old forest stand clearly has a noteworthy fly fauna. The adverse effect of the relatively small size of the mature old forest (less than 
<quantity box="[1123,1194,1592,1615]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="0" pageNumber="592" unit="m" value="100.0">100 m</quantity>
x 
<quantity box="[1226,1297,1592,1615]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.0" pageId="0" pageNumber="592" unit="m" value="500.0">500 m</quantity>
) is probably mitigated by the presence of other similar patches of mature forest in the vicinity. It should be noted that the spring of 2008 was relatively cool in the region and the weeks leading up to the capture date had been cold, with local snowfall in mid-June.
</paragraph>
